  Locus:
    Page: 64
By: Rumi
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Separation-Sin=The Mote in the Eye
Commentary: |
  This saying help show how the contemplative can with perfect objectivity
  and justice regard himself as ‘the worst of sinners’.
---
Although the sin which he had compassed was but a hair, yet that hair had
grown in his eyes.

Adam was the eye of the Eternal Light： a hair in the eye is a great
mountain.
